      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 4,\n  \"summary\": \"All iter-1 fixes (B1–B3, W1–W5) landed correctly. Role validation, duplicate-role gating, W2 primary-wins unconditional registration, W3 dictsort lockstep, and W5 CR/LF/NUL sanitization are functionally sound. One new warning-level issue introduced and one suggestion. No blocking issues. Sync/overlay paths in lifecycle.py and lifecycle_canonical.py are unbroken.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/platform/registry/hermes/templates/hermes.env.j2:63\",\n      \"issue\": \"W2 fix creates a false-positive WARNING when primary has empty bedrock credentials and an aux has real ones. When primary is absent from secrets.json, _key_compare is '|'. The aux has 'AKIA|secret', which differs, so _conflicts.append fires and the template emits '# WARNING: multiple bedrock providers attached with different API keys'. The invariant (primary-wins, no aux emission) is correct, but the warning text misrepresents the problem — the primary has no creds, not different creds. An operator reading this during a missing-secret failure will be sent on the wrong chase.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a distinct code path or comment marker for 'primary-has-no-creds' vs 'same-type-different-keys'. In the bedrock branch, if _key_compare is '|' (empty both), register the slot but skip the _conflicts.append — and raise from the upstream caller instead. The canonical path already raises AgentConfigError on missing bedrock primary creds in build_render_inputs; this edge case is legacy-template-only, so the operator-facing path that matters is already covered.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:386\",\n      \"issue\": \"AUXILIARY_SLOTS is imported in a second standalone deferred-import statement inside build_render_inputs, despite provider_attachments already being imported at line 251-253 (as `n