rdering for injection safety.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/platform/registry/hermes/templates/hermes.env.j2:13-14\",\n      \"issue\": \"The `shell_quote` macro (in-template Jinja, ansible path) strips CR/LF/NUL via Python's `_shell_quote` lookalike — confirmed correct. However the legacy `yaml_quote` macro at `hermes-config.yaml.j2:13-14` only replaces `'` with `''` and does NOT strip CR/LF/NUL from `_aux_model` (line 151). A newline in a YAML single-quoted scalar folds to a space (per YAML 1.2 §7.3.3) so there is no structural injection risk — the YAML parser will not see a new key. A NUL byte is a data-corruption concern (some parsers truncate the scalar at NUL) but not an injection path. The canonical path correctly uses `| yq` which does strip NUL/CR/LF.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Extend the `yaml_quote` Jinja macro to strip CR/LF/NUL before the single-quote escaping: `'{{ value | string | replace('\\\\x00','') | replace('\\\\r','') | replace('\\\\n','') | replace(\\\"'\\\", \\\"''\\\") }}'`. This matches the behavior of Python's `_yaml_quote` and eliminates the NUL-truncation risk for the ansible-driven render path.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:392-410\",\n      \"issue\": \"B1 fix is exact-string membership against AUXILIARY_SLOTS — correct. However `role = entry.get('role', '')` is read without `.strip()` before the membership check. A role value like `'vision '` (trailing space) raises `AgentConfigError` rather than matching the slot. This is the safe/strict side of ambiguity, but it means a hosts.json produced by a lenient upstream writer could cause a confusing error message ('invalid role vision ') instead of normalizing the value.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Consider `role = (entry.get('role') or '').strip()` before the AUXILIARY_SLOTS check. This is a UX improvement, not a security fix — strict matching is the correct security posture.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Apply W5 CR/LF/NUL filter to `hermes-env.canonical.j2:30` (`{{ _c.type | replace('\\\\n','') ... }}`) to match the defense-in-depth applied to the legacy template. The Python whitelist is not a template-level control.\",\n    \"B1 (role injection), W2 (bedrock dedup ordering), W5 (legacy env comment) are all correctly resolved — no rework needed.\",\n    \"Confirm there is no code path that calls `_build_provider_env_views` without first routing through the `render_hermes` whitelist gate at `render.py:875-879`. If one exists (direct test helper, future renderer), the canonical template's unsanitized `_c.type` becomes exploitable.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 6,\n    \"domain\": \"template-injection / credential-handling / env-file generation\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
