issue\": \"CONFLUENCE_SPACES_FILTER and JIRA_PROJECTS_FILTER are conditionally emitted inside the MCP server `env:` block in the legacy YAML template. The canonical render path has no equivalent: `atlassian_views` in render.py:938-947 is built from only five keys (slug, url, email, token, confluence_url), and hermes-config.canonical.yaml.j2 has no branch for these fields. A `clawctl agent configure` (legacy path) that writes these filter settings is followed by a `clawctl agent sync` (canonical path) that silently replaces the MCP block without them — data-loss on every sync.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add `confluence_spaces_filter` and `jira_projects_filter` keys to the `atlassian_views` dict in render.py (reading from `CONFLUENCE_SPACES_FILTER` / `JIRA_PROJECTS_FILTER` credentials), and emit them conditionally in hermes-config.canonical.yaml.j2 mirroring the legacy pattern. Add a lockstep test that verifies a configure-then-sync round-trip preserves filter settings.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py:598-648\",\n      \"issue\": \"test_multi_aux_yaml_ordering_matches covers `vision` + `web_extract` (both alphabetically after `title_generation`). Neither test exercises a role that sorts before `title_generation` (e.g., `approval`, `mcp`, `curator`). Both families emit the default `title_generation` before the sorted aux loop, so a role \u003c `title_generation` would not appear in alphabetical position. The current test set does not verify the two families agree on this edge case.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a lockstep parity test pairing the default title_generation with an `approval` aux slot. Assert `list(legacy_yaml['auxiliary'].keys()) == list(canonical_yaml['auxiliary'].keys())` for that config.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:860\",\n      \"issue\": \"`render_hermes()` validates the primary provider type (line 876) but has no corresponding check on `inputs.auxiliary_providers[*].type`. An unknown aux type (not bedrock, not in `_BEARER_API_KEY_TYPES`, not ollama) silently falls through `_build_provider_env_views` with no key emitted and no error, and renders `provider: \\\"auto\\\"` in the YAML auxiliary block. The silent fall-through is inconsistent with render_hermes's stated contract of failing loudly on unsupported configurations.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"After the primary type guard at render.py:876, add a loop over `inputs.auxiliary_providers` that raises `AgentConfigError` if any aux.type is not in `_HERMES_SUPPORTED_PROVIDERS`.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Apply CR/LF/NUL filter to `_c.type` in hermes-env.canonical.j2:30 to match the W5 fix in the legacy template — the canonical path has a narrower injection surface but it is real via the pure-function API.\",\n    \"Thread CONFLUENCE_SPACES_FILTER and JIRA_PROJECTS_FILTER through the atlassian_views dict in render.py and emit them in hermes-config.canonical.yaml.j2 to close the configure→sync data-loss gap.\",\n    \"Add aux-type validation in render_hermes() mirroring the primary-type guard so the pure-function API enforces the same safety contract as build_render_inputs().\",\n    \"Extend the lockstep parity tests to include a role that alphabetically precedes 'title_generation' (e.g., 'approval') to pin the default-title_gen-first emission ordering across both families.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 5,\n    \"domain\": \"hermes-templates/render-pipeline\",\n    \"iter1_fixes_verified\": [\"W1-default_title_gen_map-threading\", \"W3-dictsort-lockstep\", \"W5-crlf-nul-legacy-env\"],\n    \"new_findings\": [\"W-canonical-env-_c.type-unfiltered\", \"W-lockstep-confluence-jira-filter-gap\"],\n    \"pre_existing_confirmed\": [\"CONFLUENCE_SPACES_FILTER-lockstep-gap\", \"aux-type-silent-passthrough\"]\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
